The paper deals with online hashing for large-scale image datasets, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves graph regularization and discrete optimization, which are also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper uses a supervised learning approach, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
